    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-03T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-02T15:35:00-05:00" n="1176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1162</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-11-03T13:00:00-05:00"
                        notBefore="1914-11-03T00:00:00+03:25">
                        <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                    </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 3, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Russian officers have seized Turkish and Austrian Consuls and archives at Tabriz
                    and sent them to Russia. Germans are threatened and Consul was feloniously
                    assaulted. Paddock has extended temporary refuge and protection to
                    panic-stricken German Consul and subjects. Russians will arrest, expel, and
                    perhaps deport all Germans. Wire instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Telegram]</note>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1914-11-05T22:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Your undated. The Legation should maintain the attitude of strictest
                        neutrality in conformity with the proclamation issued by the President.</p>
                    <p>You will instruct the Consul at Tabriz that he should use the greatest care
                        and discretion in extending protection to nationals other than American
                        citizens.</p>
                    <p>Up to the present time the United States Government has not been requested to
                        take charge of German or Austrian interests in Persia.</p>
                    <p rend="right">
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
